verbs.description: unbank (third-person singular simple present unbanks, present participle unbanking, simple past and past participle unbanked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remove a bank from; to open by, or as if by, the removal of a bank.
examples: We may forget them, ay forget the world, Its cares, its kingdoms, and unbank the hours

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make (a fire) burn up by raking off the ashes from the top, opening draughts, etc.
